                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Veṅkaṭēśa Perumāl temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>1446 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription mentions Eṟṟa-Kampayadēva, a Śāḷuva chieftain. The details of date given, viz., Śaka 1368, Kshaya, Tulā ba. 5, Monday, Mṛigaśīrsham, regularly correspond to 1446 A.D., October 10, Monday, ·35 ·04</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records a gift of 1000 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> by the above-mentioned chief for food offerings to god Tiruvēṅgadam-udaiyān for his own merit.</p>						
                                                        						
                            
                        </summary>
